# Frontend Development Guidelines

## TypeScript Standards

- Use TypeScript strictly - no `any` types unless absolutely necessary
- Define proper interfaces and types for all components and functions
- Use type imports when importing types: `import type { ... }`

## Component Structure

- Follow established file naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper prop types and default values
- Export components as named exports

## Styling and UI

- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Follow Radix UI patterns for complex components
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Use CSS variables for theme values

## State Management

- Use React Query (@tanstack/react-query) for server state
- Use React hooks for local component state
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Handle loading and error states consistently

## Supabase Integration

- Use the established Supabase client patterns
- Implement proper authentication flows
- Follow RLS patterns for data access
- Use real-time subscriptions where appropriate
